dataIdInfo.idPurp: A polyline feature class which includes stormwater infrastructure such as pipes and open channels.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Linear stormwater features, including pipes, ditches, and perennial streams digitized using ArcGIS online, and quality checked in ArcGIS Desktop. Data has been verified in the Lick Run watershed (2015) and is being updated in Tinker, Glade, Carvin, and Lick Run - Norfolk Southern watersheds for 2016. Data in the remainder of the City has not been checked for quality control.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Data collection by City of Roanoke Stormwater Staff (2015 - 2016) using iPads and ArcGIS Collector. Data storage by City of Roanoke Dept. of Technology: 215 Church Ave. SW, Roanoke, VA 24011; Phone: 540-853-1300, Fax: 540-853-6044; Email: gis@roanokeva.gov. Database schema, attribute and geometry quality control by Dr. Randy Dymond's Urban Stormwater Research Group, Virginia Tech, Blacksburg, VA. Email: dymond@vt.edu
